This paper is about an optimization stack for deep learning, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) since deep learning is widely used in these fields. The paper also discusses optimization challenges specific to deep learning, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the ability to target new hardware accelerator back-ends, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category as well.
